68-.83 2.114-1.223 3.584-1.223 3.48 0 8.215 2.198 12.16 5.977 2.836 2.715 4.888 5.834 5.781 8.782.835 2.757.544 4.993-.818 6.298-.853.816-2.086 1.23-3.595 1.23-.902 0-1.903-.148-2.979-.448Z\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\" style=\"\"></path><path d=\"M16.813.521c-3.383.941-6.931 3.075-9.991 6.006C.25 12.823-1.931 20.596 1.855 24.223 3.111 25.426 4.843 26 6.838 26c4.016 0 9.096-2.33 13.486-6.536 6.57-6.295 8.752-14.068 4.967-17.695C24.067.597 22.366 0 20.34 0c-1.09 0-2.273.173-3.526.521ZM3.233 22.903c-1.358-1.3-1.645-3.53-.81-6.282.892-2.945 2.944-6.06 5.777-8.774 2.83-2.714 6.083-4.679 9.156-5.535 1.078-.299 2.079-.448 2.98-.448 1.503 0 2.73.412 3.578 1.225 1.356 1.3 1.644 3.531.81 6.282-.893 2.944-2.945 6.06-5.777 8.774-3.942 3.777-8.673 5.977-12.146 5.977-1.464 0-2.704-.39-3.568-1.219Z\" fill-rule=\"nonzero\" style=\"\"></path></g></svg></a></div></div></div></div><p>Heavy-duty truck manufacturer AB Volvo is setting aside $423.2 million to cover losses from suspending its business in Russia because of the invasion of Ukraine.</p><p>Among major truck makers, the Sweden-based company had the greatest exposure to Russia, counting about 3% of its net sales there. The provision, mostly due to financial services, will impact Q1 operating income. Volvo reports earnings on April 22.</p><p>Russia’s six-week-long invasion of Ukraine has seen more than 4 million Ukrainians flee abroad, killed or injured thousands, and turned cities into rubble, <a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/business/ab-volvo-takes-423-mln-provision-amid-russia-ukraine-uncertainty-2022-04-08/?utm_source=seeking_alpha&amp;utm_campaign=rta-stock-news&amp;messageid=2900&amp;mailingid=27301705&amp;serial=27301705.291&amp;utm_term=27301705.291&amp;source=email_2900&amp;utm_medium=email#:~:text=STOCKHOLM%2C%20April%208%20%28Reuters%29,truck%20maker%20said%20on%20Friday\">Reuters reported.</a> That has led to sweeping sanctions on its leaders and companies.</p><p>“The Volvo Group expresses its deepest sympathy with all the people suffering due to the devastating war in Ukraine and is committed to supporting affected employees, families and communities,” the company said <a href=\"https://prnmedia.prnewswire.com/news-releases/financial-impact-on-volvo-group-due-to-the-war-in-ukraine-301520727.html\">in a statement Friday.</a></p><p>Volvo’s Group net sales were $39.3 billion in 2021. The company’s business in Russia includes a production site in Kaluga, near Moscow. It can produce 15,000 vehicles per year  and employed more than 600 people, according to Reuters.</p><p>Volvo shares (<a href=\"https://www.barchart.com/stocks/quotes/VLVLY/overview\">OTC: VLVLY</a>) have lost a quarter of their value since the start of the year. Shortages of components and freight capacity bear the blame amid production disruptions and increased costs.</p><div class=\"stream-item stream-item-in-post stream-item-inline-post aligncenter\"><div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1550535422102-0\" data-google-query-id=\"COa4lbWN1PcCFQnhvAodRHEIzQ\">  <div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot2_0__container__\" style=\"border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center;\"><iframe id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot2_0\" name=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot2_0\" title=\"3rd party ad content\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" scrolling=\"no\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" frameborder=\"0\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Advertisement\" tabindex=\"0\" srcdoc=\"\" data-google-container-id=\"2\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom;\" data-load-complete=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></div><p>The company has total assets of approximately 9 billion Swedish crowns ($952 million) related to Russia, two-thirds of which could be materialized in coming years.</p><p>Volvo Group is the parent of Volvo Trucks North America and Mack Trucks. They build all heavy- and medium duty trucks for the U.S. and Canada in Virginia and Pennsylvania.</p><h2 id=\"h-related-articles\"><strong>Related articles:</strong></h2><p><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/maersk-orders-110-electric-class-8-trucks-from-volvo\">Maersk orders 110 electric Class 8 trucks from Volvo</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/q4-deliveries-rise-but-orders-constricted-at-volvo-trucks\">Q4 deliveries rise but orders constricted at Volvo Trucks</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/volvo-sees-clear-road-ahead-to-zero-tailpipe-emissions-by-2050\">Volvo sees clear road ahead to zero tailpipe emissions by 2050</a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/author/alanadler\"><em>Click for more FreightWaves articles by Alan Adler.</em></a></p><div class=\"stream-item stream-item-in-post stream-item-inline-post aligncenter\"><div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1550535506376-0\" data-google-query-id=\"COe4lbWN1PcCFQnhvAodRHEIzQ\">  <div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot3_0__container__\" style=\"border: 0pt none; margin: auto; text-align: center;\"><iframe id=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot3_0\" name=\"google_ads_iframe_/21776187881/fw-responsive-main_content-slot3_0\" title=\"3rd party ad content\" width=\"468\" height=\"60\" scrolling=\"no\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" frameborder=\"0\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Advertisement\" tabindex=\"0\" srcdoc=\"\" data-google-container-id=\"3\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom;\" data-load-complete=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></div><p></p><div class=\"upcoming_events\"><div class=\"upcoming_left\"><h2>Register today for the Future of Supply Chain #FOSC22</h2><p>The leading voices in supply chain are coming to Rogers, Arkansas, on May 9-10.</p><p><i>*limited term pricing available.</i></p></div><div class=\"upcoming_right\"> <a href=\"https://bit.ly/FOSCTickets-Article\" target=\"_blank\">Learn More</a></div></div><div class=\"post-bottom-meta post-bottom-tags post-tags-modern\"><div cl